High-risk clients; High-risk deal types; 
A client is considered high-risk if their risk_profile is 'High'; 
A deal type is considered high-risk if its risk_level is 'High'; 
Alerts are triggered for trades with high-risk deal types and clients with high-risk profiles.

High-volume trades refer to trades that exceed the average trade quantity; 
A report ID is a unique identifier assigned to each trade based on the exchange and trade date, with more recent trades given a higher report ID; 
The maximum quantity traded refers to the largest quantity traded for each report ID and exchange.
